Market Update: The Capital Shift Nobody Is Talking About


The AI funding boom had a silent architect. Between 2024 and 2025, Middle
Eastern sovereign wealth funds tripled their direct VC deployment =E2=80=94=
 from
$13.3B to $42.5B =E2=80=94 while committing hundreds of billions more indir=
ectly
through LP positions in top US and Asian funds. Saudi PIF, ADIA, QIA, and
Mubadala didn=E2=80=99t just participate in the AI supercycle. They built i=
t.


On March 3, 2026, Iran went to war. And the calculus changed overnight.


Saudi PIF =E2=80=94 which entered 2026 with $1.15 trillion in assets =E2=80=
=94 has since
slashed construction budgets by 60%, cancelled The Line, and formalized an
80/20 domestic reallocation for its next five-year strategy. Saudi non-oil
PMI posted its sharpest monthly drop in survey history. Gulf funds are
going pencils-down on new international commitments. Bankers are quietly
leaving Dubai and Doha.


Here=E2=80=99s the harder question: what happens to the global innovation e=
conomy
when its biggest funder decides to rebuild at home?


We see this playing out in three ways. First, Gulf capital doesn=E2=80=99t
disappear =E2=80=94 it redirects toward AI companies with deployable expert=
ise in
the region. Defense AI, sovereign compute, and data infrastructure remain
priority categories. Second, every major economy is now accelerating its
own AI buildout: Saudi=E2=80=99s HUMAIN, Japan=E2=80=99s Sovereign AI progr=
am with
Microsoft, India=E2=80=99s compute push. The world is moving from one globa=
l AI
stack to many regional ones. Third, and most structurally: the LP base for
venture capital is about to shift. Funds that relied on Gulf sovereign
money as their anchor LP will need to rebuild from a different base.


For us, this is a tailwind. We back AI categories that governments and
enterprises must fund regardless of geopolitics. And we are raising Contra
VC from operators, family offices, and institutional allocators =E2=80=94 a=
 base
built for the next decade, not the last one.


Thought Piece: Your Company Is Invisible Where It Matters Most

Search has fundamentally changed. Today users are not running search on
Google, are asking questions to ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Google AI
Overviews. And they get a synthesized answer that names two or three
vendors. If your company isn=E2=80=99t one of them, you don=E2=80=99t exist=
 in that moment
of intent.

Why This Is Happening Now

ChatGPT now has 883 million monthly users. Google AI Overviews appear in
55% of all searches. Gartner projects that traditional search engine volume
will drop 25% by end of 2026. This is not a prediction =E2=80=94 it is alre=
ady the
behavior of your buyers.

A Real Example: What Happened to HubSpot

HubSpot built one of the most powerful SEO moats in B2B SaaS. Millions of
monthly visitors. Page-one rankings for almost every marketing term
imaginable. Then AI Overviews arrived, and traffic from informational
queries =E2=80=94 the kind HubSpot dominated =E2=80=94 dropped sharply. Vis=
itors who used
to land on a HubSpot blog post and convert into leads were now getting a
summarized answer from Google with no click required. HubSpot=E2=80=99s SEO=
 moat
didn=E2=80=99t disappear. It just stopped generating the same number of doo=
rs into
its funnel.

This is the AEO problem. Answer Engine Optimization is the discipline of
ensuring your brand gets cited when AI answers your buyers=E2=80=99 questio=
ns. And
the data is striking: AI-referred visitors convert at 4.4x the rate of
standard organic visitors. They=E2=80=99re not browsing. They=E2=80=99re bu=
ying.

The Playbook for Founders

   - Write for extraction, not engagement. AI systems cite content that is
   structured, concise, and factually clear. A 60-word definition of what y=
our
   product does is more citation-worthy than a 2,000-word thought leadershi=
p
   piece.


   - Own your narrative before Reddit does. If you don=E2=80=99t define you=
r brand
   consistently across your site, press coverage, and third-party sources, =
AI
   will define you using whatever it finds =E2=80=94 including your unhappy=
 customer=E2=80=99s
   LinkedIn post.


   - Track citations, not just traffic. Tools like Profound and BrightEdge
   now show your AI citation share by query. This is the new organic share =
of
   voice. Know yours.

It is for this reason we recently invested in Lapis Labs
<https://h9zn9.r.a.d.sendibm1.com/mk/cl/f/sh/OycZvHuFo2WpIx1TPMWsQSTp/Rg7-G=
c1W2-zT>
=E2=80=94
building AI to create on-brand ads in any language, across any platform.
Distribution is the new moat, and AEO is how you build it.


